originalText.text: After 3 months they up your rate... Mine was increased almost 20%; when I called, the representative told me this is standard practice.  They also automatically enrolled me in an insurance plan which was higher than their cheapest.  The facilities are nice but it seems like they try to trick you and up your rate later when you've moved or don't have means of changing storage facilities.  Doesn't sit well, but it leaves you without much recourse.  Thumbs down

originalText.text:
We are using the Manhattan mini storage like for over a decade, different locations, 1 at the time, the smallest unit that they have.
But for the last 2 years, we tried this location out of having no other options but this one.
Well, we did the right choice choosing this location and we are extremely pleased with everything.
They have always a promotions going on for the new units.
They have all possible supplies for moving if you missed something.
Super Friendly and understanding personal (only if you are really explain them your situation).
Responsive customer support.
From just having 1 medium size unit 2 years ago which can fit like a studio/1 bedroom apartment, NOW, we have 3 big sized units big enough to fit the furniture for up to 3 bedrooms apartment and even have some room for a little extra ( only if you are good in playing a TETRIS GAME)ðŸ˜œ.
In over 2 years we never had such problems like we did with other locations : mice damaging the stuff or even cockroaches because it is the major issue at many other locations that we tried over last 12 years and just in general in NYC .
Just great

originalText.text:
The nonprofit that I work with has been storing our supplies in the Manhattan Mini Storage at 543 West 43rd in Manhattan for many, many years. The location is bright, clean, and temperature controlled. A few years ago, they underwent an expansion and modernization of parts of the property, and there is a nice variety of storage unit sizes and locations. There are also a few parking spots in a loading bay, which is so convenient.

The staff are always friendly and helpful. On the few occasions that Iâ€™ve needed something, I have always felt like the staff were happy to accommodate. To this point, I received excellent support from staff member Lawrence Turk yesterday while arranging to switch to a larger storage unit for our nonprofit. The paperwork was handled smoothly and efficiently, and Lawrence made sure my coworker and I had all the info and everything we needed to complete our relocation. All my questions were answered, and Lawrence was very friendly during my various stops downstairs by the office during the move. Consider this location the next time youâ€™re looking for somewhere to store your things.
